: Government Hospital Project Sri Lanka | Period : | 2017-2017 | Roles and responsibilities: Involved in Post Contract  Take off for Monthly valuation.  Prepare the interim valuation for payment Application.  I dent ifyi n g an d c alc ul at in g t h e va ri at i on due t o t h e c h an ges in t h e E mployer’s Req ui remen t and other related situations as applicable as per the contract.  Identify the items / activities vary from the original scope of work and prepare & submit the newrate analysis for the items vary from the tender BOQ.  Preparation of BOQ for the subcontractors’ packages.  Prepare the Payment certificate for Sub Contractor.  Assessments of scope of works and the contract sum for the subcontractors.  Purchase related all responsibility - New Vendor Development, Price Negotiation with vendor,PO releasing, Material Delivery and Payment etc.  Procurement of all kind of material (Civil, Mechanical, & Electrical).  Ensure the quality & quantity of material purchase at site.  Update the value of work done for internal Budget authorization.  Assisting to the Contract Manager in preparing Claims and other related documents. Involved in Pre Contract  Evaluating tender documents, drawings, & schedules.  Preparation of Queries for the packages from the clients.  Quantity take off for all elements based on pricing preambles and compiling the tender BOQ with description.  Preparation of BOQ, contract documents, Estimation and pricing activity.  Floating Enquiries to Suppliers / Manufacturers.  Based on Clients budget constraints for any specific project, carrying out Value engineering studies.  Comparison Studies based on suppliers Quotations.  Negotiations with consultants, suppliers & sub-contractors on technical and commercialaspects of product.  Calculating a final figure for the estimated cost, supplemented by adjustments for overheads and profit, and presenting a tender price.  Prepare and maintain a directory of suppliers, contractors and subcontractors.  Prepare estimates of probable costs of materials, Labour and equipment for constructionprojects based on contract bids, quotations, schematic drawings and specifications."}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\QS AASHIQ CV.pdf', 'Name: As. Aashiq Ahamed

